{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}

{% set bodyClass = "post" %}

{% block pageHeader %}
<header>
    <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
</header>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="content">
    {{ content | safe }}
    <p>The example is to to use UIOptions with Personal Data Server. The Personal Data Server allows the user
        to save and load interface preferences which have been applied to websites using UIOptions.</p>
    <p>Prerequisite: Personal Data Server should be running at <code>http://localhost:3000</code>.
        Refer to <a href="https://github.com/fluid-project/personal-data-server">Personal Data Server Documentation</a>
        about how to start Personal Data Server locally.
    </p>
    <h2>How to use:</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Click "Login to Personal Data Server Using a Google Account" to log in to Personal Data Server</li>
        <li>Once logged in successfully, the userâ€™s saved preferences will be fetched from the Personal Data
            Server and merged with any local preferences that the user selected before logging in.</li>
        <li>Any changes you make to preferences will now be automatically saved to the Personal Data Server.</li>
        <li>Click "Logout" to log out of Personal Data Server. The UIOptions preferences are restored to those
            in effect before logging in.</li>
    </ol>

    <button id="login">Login to Personal Data Server Using a Google Account</button>
    <button id="logout">Logout</button>

    <div id="message" role="region" aria-live="polite"></div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
